@Node Main "irchat"
@Next "Introduction"

   Welcome to the documentation of irchat.el, the GNU Emacs interface to
Internet Relay Chat. irchat.el provides all the necessary IRC features,
combined with the easy extensibility of GNU Emacs.


 @{" Introduction " Link "Introduction"} What is irchat.el?
 @{" Etiquette " Link "Etiquette"} 	How to behave in IRC.
 @{" Overview " Link "Overview"} 	Why use IRC in GNU Emacs?
 @{" Installing " Link "Installing"} 	How to get irchat.el up and running?
 @{" Using " Link "Using"}  	Using irchat.el
 @{" Commands " Link "Commands"} 	IRC Commands in irchat.el
 @{" Customizing " Link "Customizing"} 	Customizing irchat.el
 @{" Authors " Link "Authors"} 	Reporting bugs etc.


@EndNode

@Node "Introduction" "irchat/Introduction"
@Next "Etiquette"
@Prev "Main"
@Toc "Main"

Introduction
************

   What is irchat.el?

   Irchat.el is a GNU Emacs client for the Internet Relay Chat protocol.
Study the documentation accompanying the server. Make sure to read the
etiquette file. Irchat.el is designed to be easily modifiable if you
know emacs-lisp and understand the meaning of hooks.
Files that are needed to run irchat are: irchat.el, irchat-commands.el
and irchat-handle.el.
This document describes version 2.1 of irchat. It runs with servers up
to and including ircd2.6.1.


@EndNode

